Anonymous Sun 01 Jul 2018 23:28:59 No.16721318 Report
Quoted By: >>16721826
>>16721138
Some suggest just sitting down and forcing yourself to write something, anything.
It then apparently helps you to practice for when inspiration hits.
For myself, that doesn't work so well.
What I do is with switch temporarily to another project to get the old creative juices flowing, and then come back to it.
Or, I just go do other stuff, like take a walk, watch a movie etc.
While doing so I then just spitball ideas in my had about the story and characters.
It usually helps if I'm stuck on something.
That is pretty much how my latest chapter if Poolboy Blues came to be.
All in all, you got to find your own rhythm, you cant force it if you're not in the mood.
Take your time.
